Spot - Class in it.cnr.isti.hpc.dexter.spot
A spot consists of: the mention (i.e. the common anchor used to link the entities) the list of entities related to the current mention in the knowledge base the frequency of the mention: how many times the mention occurs in the collection (as link or simple text) the link frequency of the mention: how many times the mention occurs in the collection as a link to an entity the idf score of the mentions The spot is not document related, but collection related.
Spot(String) - Constructor for class it.cnr.isti.hpc.dexter.spot.Spot
Builds a spot from a textual mention
Spot(String, List<Entity>, int, int) - Constructor for class it.cnr.isti.hpc.dexter.spot.Spot
Creates the spot, and associates the entities that can be referred by the mention, how many times the mention occurs as an anchor-text in Wikipedia and how many articles that contain the mention as anchor or simple text (i.e. document frequency of the spot).
